        "note_tweet": {
          "entities": {},
          "text": "People are blaming Dario as if he started everything. I don’t see it that way.\n\nFable 5 was released publicly. Then the Trump administration used national-security/export-control grounds to restrict access by foreign nationals. Faced with that, Anthropic did not choose to keep Fable 5 alive only for a privileged subset of users. They took it down for everyone.\n\nYou can criticize Dario. But pretending he alone destroyed Fable 5 ignores the government intervention, the export-control pressure, and the new path where only trusted partners may get access again.\n\nTo me, this looks less like accountability and more like people screaming at the most visible target because they lost Fable 5. Honestly, the companies standing at a distance and quietly benefiting from this mess look far more cynical."
        },
